A   couple of   times recently, I have contrasted Bill Ackman=E2=80=99s old=
-school approach to managing a hedge fund =E2=80=94=C2=A0he=E2=80=99s a fam=
ous guy, he makes concentrated=C2=A0high-conviction bets on stocks, he does=
n=E2=80=99t hedge much =E2=80=94=C2=A0with the more scientific modern appro=
ach of multimanager multistrategy =E2=80=9Cpod shop=E2=80=9D funds, which h=
ire many portfolio managers to make distinct bets, hedging out factor expos=
ure and isolating only their alpha, their skill, their excess returns that =
are not correlated to the broader market. I noted that the old-school appro=
ach seems to have become less popular with institutional investors, and tha=
t the pod shops have an advantage in=C2=A0raising money and   charging fees=
 these days. Ackman=E2=80=99s simple legible approach, meanwhile, appeals t=
o retail investors, and he=E2=80=99s out raising money from ordinary invest=
ors=C2=A0and offering lower fees.
But I neglected to mention one incredibly important advantage of Ackman=E2=
=80=99s approach, which is that if you do it right, you don=E2=80=99t have =
to=C2=A0do=C2=A0much. Pick like 10 stocks that are going to go up, buy them=
 all, and then chill. Oh, if the stocks go=C2=A0down, that creates a lot of=
 work for you: You might have to sell them and buy other stocks (that will =
go up), you might have to reevaluate your process and rethink your life cho=
ices, maybe you have to fire an analyst and hire a new one, plus you are go=
ing to be spending a lot of time calling up your investors and reassuring t=
hem so they don=E2=80=99t withdraw their money.
  [2]
 But you are trying to pick stocks that go up, ideally ones that go up more=
 than the rest of the market, and if you succeed then you=E2=80=99re done f=
or the year. Pick stocks, buy them, watch them go up, go to the beach. Or g=
o on Twitter! (Or, now, X.) Spend your days getting in fights online, becau=
se your lavishly gainful employment only requires like 45 minutes of work p=
er year.
Oh, no,=C2=A0I=E2=80=99m exaggerating; obviously the people who pick 10 goo=
d stocks usually spend most of their waking hours analyzing their stocks, w=
