c;"> Ted Chiang=E2=80=99s essay</a> arguing that popular fears about runawa=
y artificial intelligence are=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>about modern corpor=
ate capitalism, that modern corporations actually do what we worry superint=
elligent AIs might one day do. =E2=80=9CConsider,=E2=80=9D writes Chiang:=
=C2=A0=E2=80=9CWho pursues their goals with monomaniacal focus, oblivious t=
o the possibility of negative consequences? Who adopts a scorched-earth app=
roach to increasing market share?=E2=80=9D Here, the AI chatbot was benevol=
ent and human; the corporation was not.</p>
